TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed beforefieldinit CompiledQuery extends System.Object

Docs.summary: Represents a cached LINQ to Entities query.

remarks.format:
## Remarks Provides for compilation and caching of queries for reuse. Conceptually this class contains a single `Compile` method with several overloads. You call the `Compile` method to create a new delegate to represent the compiled query. The delegate, when invoked with the <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> input parameter and other parameter values, produces some result (such as an <xref:System.Linq.IQueryable%601> instance). The query is translated and cached when the delegate is invoked for the first time.
## Examples The following example compiles and then invokes a query that accepts <xref:System.DateTime> and <xref:System.Decimal> input parameters and returns a sequence of orders where the order date is later than March 8, 2003 and the total due is less than $300.00:
